Number of Parallel Sessions per user

MinPasswordLength.description: Password must contain at least 8 characters (valid range 8-80)

NoUsername.description: Password cannot contain user name or reverse of user name

NoCiscoVariant.description: Password cannot contain 'cisco' or 'ocsic' or any capitalized letter variant thereinby substituing '1','|',or '!' for i, or '0' for 'o' or '$' for 's'

NoCharRepetition.description: No character can be repeated more than three times consecutively

NumChangedCharsEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather NumChangedChars should be update or not

NumChangedChars.description: Must change at least 1 character(s) when creating a new password (valid range 1-80)

NumReuseLimitEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather NumReuseLimit should be update or not

NumReuseLimit.description: Cannot reuse the last 5 passwords (valid range 3-24)

PasswordReuseDaysEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather PasswordReuseDays should be update or not

PasswordReuseDays.description: Cannot reuse password used in the last 15 days (valid range 1-365)

FailedLoginsBefLoEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather FailedLoginsBeforeLockout should be update or not

FailedLoginsBeforeLockout.description: Lock user out after 5 unsuccessful login attempts (valid range 1-10)

LockOutUserTimeEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather LockOutUserTime should be update or not

LockOutUserTime.description: Lock user out for 6 minutes (valid range 1-900)

PasswordExpiryDaysEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather PasswordExpiryDays should be update or not

PasswordExpiryDays.description: Cannot reuse password used in the last 15 days (valid range 1-365)

DaysForWarningEnable.description: Boolean flag to indicate wheather DaysForWarning should be update or not

DaysForWarning.description: Warn 15 days before password expiry (valid range 7-60)

rbacDeviceAccessGroup.title: Device Access Groups are defined parts of the network, so that user access can be limited to the parts they are assigned.
